rComments: It wasn't the lectures in particular that made this class great, but the in class writing practice---which was both fun and helpful. That said, the lectures were good too, if a bit long sometimes.

One of the best courses I have taken in UofT. You really have to be passionate about writing to succeed in this course. Professor English is knowledgeable and she cares about this course and the students.
It was a pretty easy class. You can mostly BS during discussion of the readings, and you'll do well if you hand in all the writing assignments.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]
